source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-mushroom-beef-penne-66313cf79eb2c19a07b967b1
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil (we used a 6-quart pot). Wash
and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{2}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced).

Trim and slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce} into 1⁄4-inch-thick pieces.

> Skip step if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!

Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large, preferably
high-sided, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{20%ounce} and
cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes} (6-8 minutes for 8 servings).

Turn off heat; transfer to a large #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out and discard.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{12%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (2 cups for 8 servings), then drain.

Keep empty pot handy for Step 5.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over
medium-high heat. Add onions and mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally,
until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> If browning too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Add @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @dried thyme{1%teaspoon},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1/2%tbsp} (1 TBSP for 8 servings);
cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are caramelized, ~{1-2%minutes}
more.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

In pot used for pasta, combine @Worcestershire sauce{2%tablespoon},
@beef stock concentrate{2}, @cream sauce base{8%ounce}, and 3⁄4 cup pasta
cooking water (1 1⁄4 cups for 8 servings).

Return pot to stovetop over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until sauce
has thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Stir in @mozzarella cheese{1%cup} until melted.

To pot with cheese sauce, add drained penne, beef, and onions and mushrooms.
Stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Serve pasta directly from pot, family style! Garnish with parsley.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.